commentary: Chigumbura to Dilshan, 1 run 9th ODI ton for Dilshan and the first in the World Cup. He's pleased as punch, this means a lot to him. Gets a back of length ball, he skips into line and dabs into the covers. Even as he runs, the dressing room stands up as one, while a buzz emanates from the appreciative crowd. He shouts in happiness and throws his arms up. Well played, Dilshan!

commentary: Malinga to Taylor, FOUR runs get the Pepsi folks to get in touch with Taylor. A shot needs patenting here. 'The perpendicular cut' is how we define it. It is an upper dab of sorts, but there is no room outside off. In fact, it is a short ball on off stump, Taylor just stays stable, waits for it to reach him and then opens the face of the bat to steer it straight over the keeper's head. Lovely to watch. He played it against NZ too, inexplicably, over fine leg.

commentary: Kulasekara to Taylor, no run This may be the end of Taylor, as Sri Lanka review an lbw appeal that was turned down. Height can be Taylor's only saviour. As always Kula gets the indipper to come in, Taylor tries to get across and shovel it to the leg side. It's hit him well over the pad, though Taylor was crouching as he played it, and replays say it was only clipping the bails. The review corroborates Umpire Erasmus' call.

commentary: Perera to Taylor, 1 run bad, bad night for Malinga. He's got a piece of his mind from Perera after dropping a swirler at third man. Short of a length on off, Taylor is too early on the shovel-hoick to the leg side, and gets a leading edge. He can't get into a good position and the ball slips through and lands inside the rope. Wake up, Sri Lanka!

commentary: Muralitharan to Mpofu, OUT aha, so what if the replays don't vindicate you. Murali decides to do it all by himself, lands the doosra outside leg stump and turns it around to hit the timber as Mopfu sweeps and misses. The wizard has finished his final game at home with a wicket. Sri Lanka are the first team to enter the quarters of World Cup 2011.
